qwen2.5:14b.full_ans:
{'output': 'yes'}

The documents indicate that Ugo Foscolo (born Niccolò Foscolo) was born on the Greek island of Zakynthos, which supports the statement "Ugo Foscolo was born in Greece." Despite Zakynthos being part of Greece now and formerly belonging to the Venetian Republic, it is correct to say he was born in what is today Greece.

gemma2.reason: Several sources state he was born on the Greek island of Zakynthos, which was part of the Venetian Republic at the time.  While Greece exists today,  Zakynthos held a different political affiliation during Foscolo's birth.
